Name: Bulbasaur
Flavor text: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

Name: Ivysaur
Flavor text: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

Name: Venusaur
Flavor text: Its plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

Name: Charmander
Flavor text: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

Name: Charmeleon
Flavor text: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.

Name: Charizard
Flavor text: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

Name: Squirtle
Flavor text: When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force.

Name: Wartortle
Flavor text: It is recognized as a symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it, that Wartortle is very old.

Name: Blastoise
Flavor text: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

Name: Caterpie
Flavor text: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

Name: Metapod
Flavor text: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

Name: Butterfree
Flavor text: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

Name: Weedle
Flavor text: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

Name: Kakuna
Flavor text: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

Name: Beedrill
Flavor text: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

Name: Pidgey
Flavor text: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

Name: Pidgeotto
Flavor text: This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

Name: Pidgeot
Flavor text: This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

Name: Rattata
Flavor text: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

Name: Raticate
Flavor text: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

Name: Spearow
Flavor text: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

Name: Fearow
Flavor text: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

Name: Ekans
Flavor text: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

Name: Arbok
Flavor text: The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

Name: Pikachu
Flavor text: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

Name: Raichu
Flavor text: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

Name: Sandshrew
Flavor text: It loves to bathe in the grit of dry, sandy areas. By sand bathing, the Pokémon rids itself of dirt and moisture clinging to its body.

Name: Sandslash
Flavor text: The drier the area Sandslash lives in, the harder and smoother the Pokémon’s spikes will feel when touched.

Name: Nidoran♀
Flavor text: Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging, they’ll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

Name: Nidorina
Flavor text: The horn on its head has atrophied. It’s thought that this happens so Nidorina’s children won’t get poked while their mother is feeding them.

Name: Nidoqueen
Flavor text: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor, this Pokémon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

Name: Nidoran♂
Flavor text: The horn on a male Nidoran’s forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

Name: Nidorino
Flavor text: With a horn that’s harder than diamond, this Pokémon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.

Name: Nidoking
Flavor text: When it goes on a rampage, it’s impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it’s lived with for a long time, Nidoking calms down.

Name: Clefairy
Flavor text: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

Name: Clefable
Flavor text: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

Name: Vulpix
Flavor text: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

Name: Ninetales
Flavor text: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.

Name: Jigglypuff
Flavor text: Jigglypuff has top-notch lung capacity, even by comparison to other Pokémon. It won’t stop singing its lullabies until its foes fall asleep.

Name: Wigglytuff
Flavor text: The more air it takes in, the more it inflates. If opponents catch it in a bad mood, it will inflate itself to an enormous size to intimidate them.

Name: Zubat
Flavor text: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

Name: Golbat
Flavor text: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

Name: Oddish
Flavor text: If exposed to moonlight, it starts to move. It roams far and wide at night to scatter its seeds.

Name: Gloom
Flavor text: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

Name: Vileplume
Flavor text: It has the world’s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

Name: Paras
Flavor text: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

Name: Parasect
Flavor text: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

Name: Venonat
Flavor text: Its large eyes act as radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

Name: Venomoth
Flavor text: The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

Name: Diglett
Flavor text: If a Diglett digs through a field, it leaves the soil perfectly tilled and ideal for planting crops.

Name: Dugtrio
Flavor text: A team of Diglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

Name: Meowth
Flavor text: It loves to collect shiny things. If it’s in a good mood, it might even let its Trainer have a look at its hoard of treasures.

Name: Persian
Flavor text: Getting this prideful Pokémon to warm up to you takes a lot of effort, and it will claw at you the moment it gets annoyed.

Name: Psyduck
Flavor text: Psyduck is constantly beset by headaches. If the Pokémon lets its strange power erupt, apparently the pain subsides for a while.

Name: Golduck
Flavor text: This Pokémon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.

Name: Mankey
Flavor text: An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.

Name: Primeape
Flavor text: It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

Name: Growlithe
Flavor text: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

Name: Arcanine
Flavor text: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

Name: Poliwag
Flavor text: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon’s innards showing through the skin.

Name: Poliwhirl
Flavor text: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl’s has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

Name: Poliwrath
Flavor text: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

Name: Abra
Flavor text: This Pokémon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokémon wields.

Name: Kadabra
Flavor text: Using its psychic power, Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

Name: Alakazam
Flavor text: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.

Name: Machop
Flavor text: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

Name: Machoke
Flavor text: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

Name: Machamp
Flavor text: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

Name: Bellsprout
Flavor text: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

Name: Weepinbell
Flavor text: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

Name: Victreebel
Flavor text: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

Name: Tentacool
Flavor text: Tentacool is not a particularly strong swimmer. It drifts across the surface of shallow seas as it searches for prey.

Name: Tentacruel
Flavor text: When the red orbs on Tentacruel’s head glow brightly, watch out. The Pokémon is about to fire off a burst of ultrasonic waves.

Name: Geodude
Flavor text: Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

Name: Graveler
Flavor text: Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

Name: Golem
Flavor text: Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it’s exposed to air.

Name: Ponyta
Flavor text: It can’t run properly when it’s newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

Name: Rapidash
Flavor text: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

Name: Slowpoke
Flavor text: Slow-witted and oblivious, this Pokémon won’t feel any pain if its tail gets eaten. It won’t notice when its tail grows back, either.

Name: Slowbro
Flavor text: Slowpoke became Slowbro when a Shellder bit on to its tail. Sweet flavors seeping from the tail make the Shellder feel as if its life is a dream.

Name: Magnemite
Flavor text: At times, Magnemite runs out of electricity and ends up on the ground. If you give batteries to a grounded Magnemite, it’ll start moving again.

Name: Magneton
Flavor text: This Pokémon is three Magnemite that have linked together. Magneton sends out powerful radio waves to study its surroundings.

Name: Farfetch'd
Flavor text: The stalk this Pokémon carries in its wings serves as a sword to cut down opponents. In a dire situation, the stalk can also serve as food.

Name: Doduo
Flavor text: Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokémon runs at high speed on developed legs.

Name: Dodrio
Flavor text: One of Doduo’s two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.

Name: Seel
Flavor text: Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Dewgong
Flavor text: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

Name: Grimer
Flavor text: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won’t grow in its path.

Name: Muk
Flavor text: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

Name: Shellder
Flavor text: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

Name: Cloyster
Flavor text: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

Name: Gastly
Flavor text: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

Name: Haunter
Flavor text: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

Name: Gengar
Flavor text: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar’s doing.

Name: Onix
Flavor text: As it digs through the ground, it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

Name: Drowzee
Flavor text: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

Name: Hypno
Flavor text: Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

Name: Krabby
Flavor text: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

Name: Kingler
Flavor text: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

Name: Voltorb
Flavor text: It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

Name: Electrode
Flavor text: Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.

Name: Exeggcute
Flavor text: Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs, it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

Name: Exeggutor
Flavor text: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.

Name: Cubone
Flavor text: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

Name: Marowak
Flavor text: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

Name: Hitmonlee
Flavor text: This amazing Pokémon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

Name: Hitmonchan
Flavor text: Its punches slice the air. They are launched at such high speed, even a slight graze could cause a burn.

Name: Lickitung
Flavor text: If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away, either.

Name: Koffing
Flavor text: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.

Name: Weezing
Flavor text: It mixes gases between its two bodies. It’s said that these Pokémon were seen all over the Galar region back in the day.

Name: Rhyhorn
Flavor text: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

Name: Rhydon
Flavor text: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

Name: Chansey
Flavor text: The egg Chansey carries is not only delicious but also packed with nutrition. It’s used as a high-class cooking ingredient.

Name: Tangela
Flavor text: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

Name: Kangaskhan
Flavor text: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

Name: Horsea
Flavor text: Horsea makes its home in oceans with gentle currents. If this Pokémon is under attack, it spits out pitch-black ink and escapes.

Name: Seadra
Flavor text: It’s the males that raise the offspring. While Seadra are raising young, the spines on their backs secrete thicker and stronger poison.

Name: Goldeen
Flavor text: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

Name: Seaking
Flavor text: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

Name: Staryu
Flavor text: If you visit a beach at the end of summer, you’ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.

Name: Starmie
Flavor text: This Pokémon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

Name: Mr. Mime
Flavor text: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

Name: Scyther
Flavor text: As Scyther fights more and more battles, its scythes become sharper and sharper. With a single slice, Scyther can fell a massive tree.

Name: Jynx
Flavor text: In certain parts of Galar, Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.

Name: Electabuzz
Flavor text: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

Name: Magmar
Flavor text: Magmar dispatches its prey with fire. But it regrets this habit once it realizes that it has burned its intended prey to a charred crisp.

Name: Pinsir
Flavor text: These Pokémon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker, more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

Name: Tauros
Flavor text: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

Name: Magikarp
Flavor text: It is virtually worthless in terms of both power and speed. It is the most weak and pathetic Pokémon in the world.

Name: Gyarados
Flavor text: It has an extremely aggressive nature. The Hyper Beam it shoots from its mouth totally incinerates all targets.

Name: Lapras
Flavor text: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

Name: Ditto
Flavor text: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

Name: Eevee
Flavor text: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

Name: Vaporeon
Flavor text: When Vaporeon’s fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.

Name: Jolteon
Flavor text: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.

Name: Flareon
Flavor text: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon’s body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Porygon
Flavor text: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be created via computer programming.

Name: Omanyte
Flavor text: Because some Omanyte manage to escape after being restored or are released into the wild by people, this species is becoming a problem.

Name: Omastar
Flavor text: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell, Omastar couldn’t move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.

Name: Kabuto
Flavor text: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days, making their shells harder and harder.

Name: Kabutops
Flavor text: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokémon.

Name: Aerodactyl
Flavor text: This is a ferocious Pokémon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

Name: Snorlax
Flavor text: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

Name: Articuno
Flavor text: It’s said that this Pokémon’s beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.

Name: Zapdos
Flavor text: This Pokémon has complete control over electricity. There are tales of Zapdos nesting in the dark depths of pitch-black thunderclouds.

Name: Moltres
Flavor text: It’s one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

Name: Dratini
Flavor text: Dratini dwells near bodies of rapidly flowing water, such as the plunge pools of waterfalls. As it grows, Dratini will shed its skin many times.

Name: Dragonair
Flavor text: This Pokémon lives in pristine oceans and lakes. It can control the weather, and it uses this power to fly into the sky, riding on the wind.

Name: Dragonite
Flavor text: It’s a kindhearted Pokémon. If it spots a drowning person or Pokémon, Dragonite simply must help them.

Name: Mewtwo
Flavor text: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

Name: Mew
Flavor text: When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.

Name: Chikorita
Flavor text: In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.

Name: Bayleef
Flavor text: Bayleef’s neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

Name: Meganium
Flavor text: The fragrance of Meganium’s flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe’s fighting spirit.

Name: Cyndaquil
Flavor text: Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

Name: Quilava
Flavor text: Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.

Name: Typhlosion
Flavor text: Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

Name: Totodile
Flavor text: Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile’s jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.

Name: Croconaw
Flavor text: Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

Name: Feraligatr
Flavor text: Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

Name: Sentret
Flavor text: When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.

Name: Furret
Flavor text: Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

Name: Hoothoot
Flavor text: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.

Name: Noctowl
Flavor text: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

Name: Ledyba
Flavor text: This Pokémon is very sensitive to cold. In the warmth of Alola, it appears quite lively.

Name: Ledian
Flavor text: It’s said that the patterns on its back are related to the stars in the night sky, but the details of that relationship remain unclear.

Name: Spinarak
Flavor text: With threads from its mouth, it fashions sturdy webs that won’t break even if you set a rock on them.

Name: Ariados
Flavor text: Every night, it wanders around in search of prey, whose movements it restrains by spewing threads before it bites into them with its fangs.

Name: Crobat
Flavor text: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target’s neck.

Name: Chinchou
Flavor text: Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.

Name: Lanturn
Flavor text: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea’s surface from a depth of over three miles.

Name: Pichu
Flavor text: Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.

Name: Cleffa
Flavor text: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

Name: Igglybuff
Flavor text: Igglybuff loves to sing. Its marshmallow-like body gives off a faint sweet smell.

Name: Togepi
Flavor text: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

Name: Togetic
Flavor text: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.

Name: Natu
Flavor text: It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.

Name: Xatu
Flavor text: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

Name: Mareep
Flavor text: Clothing made from Mareep’s fleece is easily charged with static electricity, so a special process is used on it.

Name: Flaaffy
Flavor text: In the places on its body where fleece doesn’t grow, its skin is rubbery and doesn’t conduct electricity. Those spots are safe to touch.

Name: Ampharos
Flavor text: The light from its tail can be seen from space. This is why you can always tell exactly where it is, which is why it usually keeps the light off.

Name: Bellossom
Flavor text: Plentiful in the tropics. When it dances, its petals rub together and make a pleasant ringing sound.

Name: Marill
Flavor text: This Pokémon uses its round tail as a float. The ball of Marill’s tail is filled with nutrients that have been turned into an oil.

Name: Azumarill
Flavor text: It spends most of its time in the water. On sunny days, Azumarill floats on the surface of the water and sunbathes.

Name: Sudowoodo
Flavor text: If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it’s a Sudowoodo, not a tree. It hides from the rain.

Name: Politoed
Flavor text: At nightfall, these Pokémon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.

Name: Hoppip
Flavor text: This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

Name: Skiploom
Flavor text: Skiploom’s flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

Name: Jumpluff
Flavor text: Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

Name: Aipom
Flavor text: As it did more and more with its tail, its hands became clumsy. It makes its nest high in the treetops.

Name: Sunkern
Flavor text: Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

Name: Sunflora
Flavor text: Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

Name: Yanma
Flavor text: Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.

Name: Wooper
Flavor text: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

Name: Quagsire
Flavor text: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.

Name: Espeon
Flavor text: By reading air currents, it can predict things such as the weather or its foe’s next move.

Name: Umbreon
Flavor text: When this Pokémon becomes angry, its pores secrete a poisonous sweat, which it sprays at its opponent’s eyes.

Name: Murkrow
Flavor text: It has a weakness for shiny things. It’s been known to sneak into the nests of Gabite—noted collectors of jewels—in search of treasure.

Name: Slowking
Flavor text: Miraculously, this former Slowpoke’s latent intelligence was drawn out when Shellder poison raced through its brain.

Name: Misdreavus
Flavor text: What gives meaning to its life is surprising others. If you set your ear against the red orbs around its neck, you can hear shrieking.

Name: Unown
Flavor text: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

Name: Wobbuffet
Flavor text: It hates light and shock. If attacked, it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.

Name: Girafarig
Flavor text: Girafarig’s rear head also has a brain, but it is small. The rear head attacks in response to smells and sounds. Approaching this Pokémon from behind can cause the rear head to suddenly lash out and bite.

Name: Pineco
Flavor text: Motionless, it hangs from trees, waiting for its bug Pokémon prey to come to it. Its favorite in Alola is Cutiefly.

Name: Forretress
Flavor text: When something approaches it, it fires off fragments of its steel shell in attack. This is not a conscious action but a conditioned reflex.

Name: Dunsparce
Flavor text: This Pokémon’s tiny wings have some scientists saying that Dunsparce used to fly through the sky in ancient times.

Name: Gligar
Flavor text: Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.

Name: Steelix
Flavor text: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

Name: Snubbull
Flavor text: It grows close to others easily and is also easily spoiled. The disparity between its face and its actions makes many young people wild about it.

Name: Granbull
Flavor text: While it has powerful jaws, it doesn’t care for disputes, so it rarely has a chance to display their might.

Name: Qwilfish
Flavor text: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent’s size.

Name: Scizor
Flavor text: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor’s body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.

Name: Shuckle
Flavor text: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

Name: Heracross
Flavor text: Heracross loves sweet sap and will go looking through forests for it. The Pokémon uses its two antennae to pick up scents as it searches.

Name: Sneasel
Flavor text: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked, it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

Name: Teddiursa
Flavor text: This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.

Name: Ursaring
Flavor text: In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.

Name: Slugma
Flavor text: Molten magma courses throughout Slugma’s circulatory system. If this Pokémon is chilled, the magma cools and hardens. Its body turns brittle and chunks fall off, reducing its size.

Name: Magcargo
Flavor text: Magcargo’s shell is actually its skin that hardened as a result of cooling. Its shell is very brittle and fragile—just touching it causes it to crumble apart. This Pokémon returns to its original size by dipping itself in magma.

Name: Swinub
Flavor text: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

Name: Piloswine
Flavor text: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

Name: Corsola
Flavor text: It will regrow any branches that break off its head. People keep particularly beautiful Corsola branches as charms to promote safe childbirth.

Name: Remoraid
Flavor text: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

Name: Octillery
Flavor text: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

Name: Delibird
Flavor text: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.

Name: Mantine
Flavor text: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.

Name: Skarmory
Flavor text: The pointed feathers of these Pokémon are sharper than swords. Skarmory and Corviknight fight viciously over territory.

Name: Houndour
Flavor text: It cooperates with others skillfully. When it becomes your partner, it’s very loyal to you as its Trainer and will obey your orders.

Name: Houndoom
Flavor text: They spew flames mixed with poison to finish off their opponents. They divvy up their prey evenly among the members of their pack.

Name: Kingdra
Flavor text: With the arrival of a storm at sea, this Pokémon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.

Name: Phanpy
Flavor text: For its nest, Phanpy digs a vertical pit in the ground at the edge of a river. It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that the area has been claimed.

Name: Donphan
Flavor text: Donphan’s favorite attack is curling its body into a ball, then charging at its foe while rolling at high speed. Once it starts rolling, this Pokémon can’t stop very easily.

Name: Porygon2
Flavor text: This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.

Name: Stantler
Flavor text: Stantler’s magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.

Name: Smeargle
Flavor text: The fluid of Smeargle’s tail secretions changes in the intensity of its hue as the Pokémon’s emotions change.

Name: Tyrogue
Flavor text: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

Name: Hitmontop
Flavor text: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

Name: Smoochum
Flavor text: If its face gets even slightly dirty, Smoochum will bathe immediately. But if its body gets dirty, Smoochum doesn’t really seem to care.

Name: Elekid
Flavor text: When a storm approaches, this Pokémon gets restless. Once Elekid hears the sound of thunder, it gets full-on rowdy.

Name: Magby
Flavor text: This Pokémon is still small and timid. Whenever Magby gets excited or surprised, flames leak from its mouth and its nose.

Name: Miltank
Flavor text: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it’s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.

Name: Blissey
Flavor text: Whenever a Blissey finds a weakened Pokémon, it will share its egg and offer its care until the other Pokémon is all better.

Name: Raikou
Flavor text: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

Name: Entei
Flavor text: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

Name: Suicune
Flavor text: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

Name: Larvitar
Flavor text: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

Name: Pupitar
Flavor text: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

Name: Tyranitar
Flavor text: Its body can’t be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

Name: Lugia
Flavor text: Lugia’s wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

Name: Ho-Oh
Flavor text: Ho-Oh’s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

Name: Celebi
Flavor text: This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

Name: Treecko
Flavor text: Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

Name: Grovyle
Flavor text: The leaves growing out of Grovyle’s body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

Name: Sceptile
Flavor text: The leaves growing on Sceptile’s body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile—it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

Name: Torchic
Flavor text: Torchic sticks with its Trainer, following behind with unsteady steps. This Pokémon breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

Name: Combusken
Flavor text: Combusken toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This Pokémon’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out 10 kicks in one second.

Name: Blaziken
Flavor text: In battle, Blaziken blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this Pokémon’s wrists burn.

Name: Mudkip
Flavor text: The fin on Mudkip’s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

Name: Marshtomp
Flavor text: The surface of Marshtomp’s body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

Name: Swampert
Flavor text: Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

Name: Poochyena
Flavor text: At first sight, Poochyena takes a bite at anything that moves. This Pokémon chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.

Name: Mightyena
Flavor text: Mightyena gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This Pokémon will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.

Name: Zigzagoon
Flavor text: It marks its territory by rubbing its bristly fur on trees. This variety of Zigzagoon is friendlier and calmer than the kind native to Galar.

Name: Linoone
Flavor text: Its fur is strong and supple. Shaving brushes made with shed Linoone hairs are highly prized.

Name: Wurmple
Flavor text: Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon’s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

Name: Silcoon
Flavor text: Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

Name: Beautifly
Flavor text: Beautifly’s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.

Name: Cascoon
Flavor text: Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.

Name: Dustox
Flavor text: Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokémon are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.

Name: Lotad
Flavor text: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

Name: Lombre
Flavor text: It is nocturnal and becomes active at nightfall. It feeds on aquatic mosses that grow in the riverbed.

Name: Ludicolo
Flavor text: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates Ludicolo’s cells, making it more powerful.

Name: Seedot
Flavor text: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

Name: Nuzleaf
Flavor text: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

Name: Shiftry
Flavor text: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe’s mind and take preemptive action.

Name: Taillow
Flavor text: Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

Name: Swellow
Flavor text: Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow’s clawed feet, preventing escape.

Name: Wingull
Flavor text: It makes its nest on sheer cliffs. Riding the sea breeze, it glides up into the expansive skies.

Name: Pelipper
Flavor text: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokémon and eggs to safety in its bill.

Name: Ralts
Flavor text: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.

Name: Kirlia
Flavor text: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

Name: Gardevoir
Flavor text: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.

Name: Surskit
Flavor text: If it’s in a pinch, it will secrete a sweet liquid from the tip of its head. Syrup made from gathering that liquid is tasty on bread.

Name: Masquerain
Flavor text: Masquerain intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns of its eyespots. If that doesn’t work, it deftly makes its escape on its set of four wings.

Name: Shroomish
Flavor text: Shroomish live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This Pokémon feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

Name: Breloom
Flavor text: Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This Pokémon’s fighting technique puts boxers to shame.

Name: Slakoth
Flavor text: Slakoth lolls around for over 20 hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This Pokémon’s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.

Name: Vigoroth
Flavor text: Vigoroth is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can’t tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This Pokémon’s stress level rises if it can’t be moving constantly.

Name: Slaking
Flavor text: Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.

Name: Nincada
Flavor text: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.

Name: Ninjask
Flavor text: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

Name: Shedinja
Flavor text: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.

Name: Whismur
Flavor text: The cry of a Whismur is over 100 decibels. If you’re close to a Whismur when it lets out a cry, you’ll be stuck with an all-day headache.

Name: Loudred
Flavor text: Loudred’s ears serve as speakers, and they can put out sound waves powerful enough to blow away a house.

Name: Exploud
Flavor text: In the past, people would use the loud voices of these Pokémon as a means of communication between distant cities.

Name: Makuhita
Flavor text: It practices its slaps by repeatedly slapping tree trunks. It has been known to slap an Exeggutor and get flung away.

Name: Hariyama
Flavor text: Although they enjoy comparing their strength, they’re also kind. They value etiquette, praising opponents they battle.

Name: Azurill
Flavor text: The ball on Azurill’s tail bounces like a rubber ball, and it’s full of the nutrients the Pokémon needs to grow.

Name: Nosepass
Flavor text: It moves less than an inch a year, but when it’s in a jam, it will spin and drill down into the ground in a split second.

Name: Skitty
Flavor text: Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.

Name: Delcatty
Flavor text: Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.

Name: Sableye
Flavor text: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it’s believed that Sableye will steal people’s spirits away.

Name: Mawile
Flavor text: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

Name: Aron
Flavor text: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

Name: Lairon
Flavor text: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore, so these Pokémon often came into conflict with humans in the past.

Name: Aggron
Flavor text: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.

Name: Meditite
Flavor text: Meditite undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this Pokémon always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.

Name: Medicham
Flavor text: It is said that through meditation, Medicham heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This Pokémon hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.

Name: Electrike
Flavor text: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

Name: Manectric
Flavor text: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.

Name: Plusle
Flavor text: Plusle always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this Pokémon shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.

Name: Minun
Flavor text: Minun is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.

Name: Volbeat
Flavor text: With the arrival of night, Volbeat emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This Pokémon is attracted by the sweet aroma of Illumise.

Name: Illumise
Flavor text: Illumise attracts a swarm of Volbeat using a sweet fragrance. Once the Volbeat have gathered, this Pokémon leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.

Name: Roselia
Flavor text: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

Name: Gulpin
Flavor text: Virtually all of Gulpin’s body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This Pokémon’s stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.

Name: Swalot
Flavor text: When Swalot spots prey, it spurts out a hideously toxic fluid from its pores and sprays the target. Once the prey has weakened, this Pokémon gulps it down whole with its cavernous mouth.

Name: Carvanha
Flavor text: It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead, it waits for other Carvanha to join it, and then the Pokémon attack as a group.

Name: Sharpedo
Flavor text: As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

Name: Wailmer
Flavor text: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

Name: Wailord
Flavor text: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

Name: Numel
Flavor text: Numel is extremely dull witted—it doesn’t notice being hit. However, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

Name: Camerupt
Flavor text: Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon’s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

Name: Torkoal
Flavor text: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

Name: Spoink
Flavor text: Spoink bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this Pokémon cannot afford to stop bouncing—if it stops, its heart will stop.

Name: Grumpig
Flavor text: Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this Pokémon uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.

Name: Spinda
Flavor text: Its steps are shaky and stumbling. Walking for a long time makes it feel sick.

Name: Trapinch
Flavor text: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.

Name: Vibrava
Flavor text: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.

Name: Flygon
Flavor text: This Pokémon hides in the heart of sandstorms it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.

Name: Cacnea
Flavor text: Cacnea lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this Pokémon shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.

Name: Cacturne
Flavor text: During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This Pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.

Name: Swablu
Flavor text: Its cottony wings are full of air, making them light and fluffy to the touch. Swablu takes diligent care of its wings.

Name: Altaria
Flavor text: As it flies in a calm and relaxed manner, Altaria performs a humming song that would enrapture any audience.

Name: Zangoose
Flavor text: Memories of battling its archrival Seviper are etched into every cell of Zangoose’s body. This Pokémon adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.

Name: Seviper
Flavor text: Seviper shares a generations-long feud with Zangoose. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This Pokémon attacks using its sword-edged tail.

Name: Lunatone
Flavor text: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.

Name: Solrock
Flavor text: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

Name: Barboach
Flavor text: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

Name: Whiscash
Flavor text: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything—if it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

Name: Corphish
Flavor text: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

Name: Crawdaunt
Flavor text: A rough customer that wildly flails its giant claws. It is said to be extremely hard to raise.

Name: Baltoy
Flavor text: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.

Name: Claydol
Flavor text: This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.

Name: Lileep
Flavor text: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

Name: Cradily
Flavor text: It has short legs and can’t walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

Name: Anorith
Flavor text: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Anorith lived in the ocean about 100,000,000 years ago, hunting with its pair of claws.

Name: Armaldo
Flavor text: After evolution, this Pokémon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.

Name: Feebas
Flavor text: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon’s marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

Name: Milotic
Flavor text: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.

Name: Castform
Flavor text: Although its form changes with the weather, that is apparently the result of a chemical reaction and not the result of its own free will.

Name: Kecleon
Flavor text: It changes its hue to blend into its surroundings. If no one takes notice of it for too long, it will pout and never reveal itself.

Name: Shuppet
Flavor text: It eats up emotions like malice, jealousy, and resentment, so some people are grateful for its presence.

Name: Banette
Flavor text: It’s a stuffed toy that was thrown away and became possessed, ever searching for the one who threw it away so it can exact its revenge.

Name: Duskull
Flavor text: If it finds bad children who won’t listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it’s said.

Name: Dusclops
Flavor text: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.

Name: Tropius
Flavor text: The bunches of fruit growing around the necks of Tropius in Alola are especially sweet compared to those in other regions.

Name: Chimecho
Flavor text: Chimecho makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this Pokémon becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.

Name: Absol
Flavor text: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

Name: Wynaut
Flavor text: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

Name: Snorunt
Flavor text: It’s said that if they are seen at midnight, they’ll cause heavy snow. They eat snow and ice to survive.

Name: Glalie
Flavor text: It has a body of ice that won’t melt, even with fire. It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere.

Name: Spheal
Flavor text: This Pokémon’s body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It’s faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.

Name: Sealeo
Flavor text: Sealeo live on top of drift ice. They go swimming when they’re on the hunt, seeking out their prey by scent.

Name: Walrein
Flavor text: Walrein form herds of 20 to 30 individuals. When a threat appears, the herd’s leader will protect the group with its life.

Name: Clamperl
Flavor text: Despite its appearance, it’s carnivorous. It clamps down on its prey with both sides of its shell and doesn’t let go until they stop moving.

Name: Huntail
Flavor text: It’s not the strongest swimmer. It wags its tail to lure in its prey and then gulps them down as soon as they get close.

Name: Gorebyss
Flavor text: The color of its body changes with the water temperature. The coloration of Gorebyss in Alola is almost blindingly vivid.

Name: Relicanth
Flavor text: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

Name: Luvdisc
Flavor text: There was an era when it was overfished due to the rumor that having one of its heart-shaped scales would enable you to find a sweetheart.

Name: Bagon
Flavor text: Bagon jumps off cliffs every day, trying to grow stronger so that someday it will be able to fly.

Name: Shelgon
Flavor text: This Pokémon has covered its body in a hard shell that has the same composition as bone. Shelgon stores energy for evolution.

Name: Salamence
Flavor text: Salamence is an unusual Pokémon in that it was able to evolve a body with wings just by constantly wishing to be able to fly.

Name: Beldum
Flavor text: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum’s sharp claws.

Name: Metang
Flavor text: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.

Name: Metagross
Flavor text: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokémon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.

Name: Regirock
Flavor text: Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.

Name: Regice
Flavor text: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as −328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.

Name: Registeel
Flavor text: Registeel’s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.

Name: Latias
Flavor text: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

Name: Latios
Flavor text: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.

Name: Kyogre
Flavor text: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

Name: Groudon
Flavor text: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

Name: Rayquaza
Flavor text: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

Name: Jirachi
Flavor text: A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this Pokémon senses danger, it will fight without awakening.

Name: Deoxys
Flavor text: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon’s chest appears to be its brain.

Name: Turtwig
Flavor text: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

Name: Grotle
Flavor text: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

Name: Torterra
Flavor text: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.

Name: Chimchar
Flavor text: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can’t extinguish the fire.

Name: Monferno
Flavor text: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

Name: Infernape
Flavor text: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

Name: Piplup
Flavor text: It doesn’t like to be taken care of. It’s difficult to bond with since it won’t listen to its Trainer.

Name: Prinplup
Flavor text: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

Name: Empoleon
Flavor text: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

Name: Starly
Flavor text: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

Name: Staravia
Flavor text: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

Name: Staraptor
Flavor text: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong. It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.

Name: Bidoof
Flavor text: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

Name: Bibarel
Flavor text: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

Name: Kricketot
Flavor text: It chats with others using the sounds of its colliding antennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.

Name: Kricketune
Flavor text: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

Name: Shinx
Flavor text: This Pokémon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.

Name: Luxio
Flavor text: By joining its tail with that of another Luxio, this Pokémon can receive some of the other Luxio’s electricity and power up its own electric blasts.

Name: Luxray
Flavor text: Luxray can see through solid objects. It will instantly spot prey trying to hide behind walls, even if the walls are thick.

Name: Budew
Flavor text: The pollen it releases contains poison. If this Pokémon is raised on clean water, the poison’s toxicity is increased.

Name: Roserade
Flavor text: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent, it lashes them with its thorny whips.

Name: Cranidos
Flavor text: A primeval Pokémon, it possesses a hard and sturdy skull, lacking any intelligence within.

Name: Rampardos
Flavor text: In ancient times, people would dig up fossils of this Pokémon and use its skull, which is harder than steel, to make helmets.

Name: Shieldon
Flavor text: A mild-mannered, herbivorous Pokémon, it used its face to dig up tree roots to eat. The skin on its face was plenty tough.

Name: Bastiodon
Flavor text: The bones of its face are huge and hard, so they were mistaken for its spine until after this Pokémon was successfully restored.

Name: Burmy
Flavor text: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

Name: Wormadam
Flavor text: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

Name: Mothim
Flavor text: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.

Name: Combee
Flavor text: The members of the trio spend all their time together. Each one has a slightly different taste in nectar.

Name: Vespiquen
Flavor text: It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with its enemies. The grubs are willing to risk their lives to defend Vespiquen.

Name: Pachirisu
Flavor text: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

Name: Buizel
Flavor text: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw. When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

Name: Floatzel
Flavor text: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

Name: Cherubi
Flavor text: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokémon that would love to make off with its small, nutrient-rich storage ball.

Name: Cherrim
Flavor text: As a bud, it barely moves. It sits still, placidly waiting for sunlight to appear.

Name: Shellos
Flavor text: This Pokémon’s habitat shapes its physique. According to some theories, life in warm ocean waters causes this variation to develop.

Name: Gastrodon
Flavor text: Its search for food sometimes leads it onto land, where it leaves behind a sticky trail of slime as it passes through.

Name: Ambipom
Flavor text: In their search for comfortable trees, they get into territorial disputes with groups of Passimian. They win about half the time.

Name: Drifloon
Flavor text: Perhaps seeking company, it approaches children. However, it often quickly runs away again when the children play too roughly with it.

Name: Drifblim
Flavor text: Some say this Pokémon is a collection of souls burdened with regrets, silently drifting through the dusk.

Name: Buneary
Flavor text: If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the Pokémon is in need of care.

Name: Lopunny
Flavor text: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds with superdestructive kicks.

Name: Mismagius
Flavor text: Feared for its wrath and the curses it spreads, this Pokémon will also, on a whim, cast spells that help people.

Name: Honchkrow
Flavor text: It will absolutely not forgive failure from or betrayal by its goons. It has no choice in this if it wants to maintain the order of the flock.

Name: Glameow
Flavor text: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

Name: Purugly
Flavor text: It would claim another Pokémon’s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

Name: Chingling
Flavor text: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound. It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.

Name: Stunky
Flavor text: From its rear, it sprays a foul-smelling liquid at opponents. It aims for their faces, and it can hit them from over 16 feet away.

Name: Skuntank
Flavor text: In its belly, it reserves stinky fluid that it shoots from its tail during battle. As this Pokémon’s diet varies, so does the stench of its fluid.

Name: Bronzor
Flavor text: It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn’t come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.

Name: Bronzong
Flavor text: Some believe it to be a deity that summons rain clouds. When angered, it lets out a warning cry that rings out like the tolling of a bell.

Name: Bonsly
Flavor text: It expels both sweat and tears from its eyes. The sweat is a little salty, while the tears have a slight bitterness.

Name: Mime Jr.
Flavor text: It mimics everyone it sees, but it puts extra effort into copying the graceful dance steps of Mr. Rime as practice.

Name: Happiny
Flavor text: Mimicking Chansey, Happiny will place an egg- shaped stone in its belly pouch. Happiny will treasure this stone.

Name: Chatot
Flavor text: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t attack it.

Name: Spiritomb
Flavor text: Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokémon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.

Name: Gible
Flavor text: Gible prefers to stay in narrow holes in the sides of caves heated by geothermal energy. This way, Gible can stay warm even during a blizzard.

Name: Gabite
Flavor text: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from a protrusion on either side of its head to probe pitch-dark caves.

Name: Garchomp
Flavor text: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.

Name: Munchlax
Flavor text: Stuffing itself with vast amounts of food is its only concern. Whether the food is rotten or fresh, yummy or tasteless—it does not care.

Name: Riolu
Flavor text: It’s exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.

Name: Lucario
Flavor text: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.

Name: Hippopotas
Flavor text: It moves through the sands with its mouth open, swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.

Name: Hippowdon
Flavor text: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.

Name: Skorupi
Flavor text: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

Name: Drapion
Flavor text: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

Name: Croagunk
Flavor text: It makes frightening noises with its poison-filled cheek sacs. When opponents flinch, Croagunk hits them with a poison jab.

Name: Toxicroak
Flavor text: It bounces toward opponents and gouges them with poisonous claws. No more than a scratch is needed to knock out its adversaries.

Name: Carnivine
Flavor text: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

Name: Finneon
Flavor text: When night falls, their pink patterns begin to shine. They’re popular with divers, so there are resorts that feed them to keep them close.

Name: Lumineon
Flavor text: Deep down at the bottom of the ocean, prey is scarce. Lumineon get into fierce disputes with Lanturn over food.

Name: Mantyke
Flavor text: Mantyke living in Galar seem to be somewhat sluggish. The colder waters of the seas in this region may be the cause.

Name: Snover
Flavor text: It lives on snowy mountains. It sinks its legs into the snow to absorb water and keep its own temperature down.

Name: Abomasnow
Flavor text: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.

Name: Weavile
Flavor text: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.

Name: Magnezone
Flavor text: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it’s being controlled by some mysterious being.

Name: Lickilicky
Flavor text: Lickilicky’s strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky’s tongue can stretch so far.

Name: Rhyperior
Flavor text: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

Name: Tangrowth
Flavor text: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

Name: Electivire
Flavor text: The amount of electrical energy this Pokémon produces is proportional to the rate of its pulse. The voltage jumps while Electivire is battling.

Name: Magmortar
Flavor text: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Togekiss
Flavor text: These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they’ve hardly been seen at all.

Name: Yanmega
Flavor text: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes’ heads instantly while flying by at high speed.

Name: Leafeon
Flavor text: Galarians favor the distinctive aroma that drifts from this Pokémon’s leaves. There’s a popular perfume made using that scent.

Name: Glaceon
Flavor text: Any who become captivated by the beauty of the snowfall that Glaceon creates will be frozen before they know it.

Name: Gliscor
Flavor text: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

Name: Mamoswine
Flavor text: This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a while, it was thought to have gone extinct.

Name: Porygon-Z
Flavor text: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z’s behavior.

Name: Gallade
Flavor text: True to its honorable-warrior image, it uses the blades on its elbows only in defense of something or someone.

Name: Probopass
Flavor text: Although it can control its units known as Mini-Noses, they sometimes get lost and don’t come back.

Name: Dusknoir
Flavor text: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.

Name: Froslass
Flavor text: After a woman met her end on a snowy mountain, her regrets lingered on. From them, this Pokémon was born. Its favorite food is frozen souls.

Name: Rotom
Flavor text: One boy’s invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom’s unique capabilities.

Name: Uxie
Flavor text: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

Name: Mesprit
Flavor text: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

Name: Azelf
Flavor text: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

Name: Dialga
Flavor text: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

Name: Palkia
Flavor text: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

Name: Heatran
Flavor text: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

Name: Regigigas
Flavor text: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

Name: Giratina
Flavor text: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

Name: Cresselia
Flavor text: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

Name: Phione
Flavor text: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

Name: Manaphy
Flavor text: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

Name: Darkrai
Flavor text: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.

Name: Shaymin
Flavor text: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

Name: Arceus
Flavor text: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.

Name: Victini
Flavor text: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

Name: Snivy
Flavor text: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

Name: Servine
Flavor text: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

Name: Serperior
Flavor text: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior’s noble eyes.

Name: Tepig
Flavor text: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

Name: Pignite
Flavor text: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.

Name: Emboar
Flavor text: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

Name: Oshawott
Flavor text: The scalchop on its stomach isn’t just used for battle—it can be used to break open hard berries as well.

Name: Dewott
Flavor text: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

Name: Samurott
Flavor text: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.

Name: Patrat
Flavor text: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

Name: Watchog
Flavor text: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.

Name: Lillipup
Flavor text: This Pokémon is courageous but also cautious. It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect information about its surroundings.

Name: Herdier
Flavor text: Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokémon. So much so that there’s a theory that Herdier was the first Pokémon to partner with people.

Name: Stoutland
Flavor text: These Pokémon seem to enjoy living with humans. Even a Stoutland caught in the wild will warm up to people in about three days.

Name: Purrloin
Flavor text: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokémon and Nickit.

Name: Liepard
Flavor text: Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokémon.

Name: Pansage
Flavor text: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

Name: Simisage
Flavor text: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.

Name: Pansear
Flavor text: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.

Name: Simisear
Flavor text: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

Name: Panpour
Flavor text: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.

Name: Simipour
Flavor text: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.

Name: Munna
Flavor text: Late at night, it appears beside people’s pillows. As it feeds on dreams, the patterns on its body give off a faint glow.

Name: Musharna
Flavor text: When dark mists emanate from its body, don’t get too near. If you do, your nightmares will become reality.

Name: Pidove
Flavor text: Where people go, these Pokémon follow. If you’re scattering food for them, be careful—several hundred of them can gather at once.

Name: Tranquill
Flavor text: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels, it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.

Name: Unfezant
Flavor text: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina, while the males outclass them in terms of speed.

Name: Blitzle
Flavor text: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

Name: Zebstrika
Flavor text: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

Name: Roggenrola
Flavor text: It’s as hard as steel, but apparently a long soak in water will cause it to soften a bit.

Name: Boldore
Flavor text: If you see its orange crystals start to glow, be wary. It’s about to fire off bursts of energy.

Name: Gigalith
Flavor text: This hardy Pokémon can often be found on construction sites and in mines, working alongside people and Copperajah.

Name: Woobat
