Flavor text: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it’s evidence that Woobat live there.

Name: Swoobat
Flavor text: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won’t be able to fly for a little while.

Name: Drilbur
Flavor text: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.

Name: Excadrill
Flavor text: It’s not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill’s rampant digging.

Name: Audino
Flavor text: Audino’s sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino’s ears.

Name: Timburr
Flavor text: It loves helping out with construction projects. It loves it so much that if rain causes work to halt, it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

Name: Gurdurr
Flavor text: It shows off its muscles to Machoke and other Gurdurr. If it fails to measure up to the other Pokémon, it lies low for a little while.

Name: Conkeldurr
Flavor text: Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more durable than normal concrete, even when the compositions of the two materials are the same.

Name: Tympole
Flavor text: Graceful ripples running across the water’s surface are a sure sign that Tympole are singing in high-pitched voices below.

Name: Palpitoad
Flavor text: It weakens its prey with sound waves intense enough to cause headaches, then entangles them with its sticky tongue.

Name: Seismitoad
Flavor text: The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.

Name: Throh
Flavor text: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles, Throh’s belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer’s sweat.

Name: Sawk
Flavor text: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength, it’s best to quietly pass by.

Name: Sewaddle
Flavor text: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.

Name: Swadloon
Flavor text: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

Name: Leavanny
Flavor text: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.

Name: Venipede
Flavor text: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species, but when the two meet, a huge fight ensues.

Name: Whirlipede
Flavor text: This Pokémon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.

Name: Scolipede
Flavor text: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws’ toxic spikes.

Name: Cottonee
Flavor text: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

Name: Whimsicott
Flavor text: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it’ll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.

Name: Petilil
Flavor text: Petilil appears around sources of clean water. Boiling leaves from this Pokémon’s head results in a liquid that’s sometimes used as a bug repellent.

Name: Lilligant
Flavor text: It’s believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant’s head to bloom.

Name: Basculin
Flavor text: Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch— many people release them into lakes illicitly.

Name: Sandile
Flavor text: The desert gets cold at night, so when the sun sets, this Pokémon burrows deep into the sand and sleeps until sunrise.

Name: Krokorok
Flavor text: Krokorok has specialized eyes that enable it to see in the dark. This ability lets Krokorok hunt in the dead of night without getting lost.

Name: Krookodile
Flavor text: This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sands. Krookodile’s mighty jaws can bite through heavy plates of iron with almost no effort at all.

Name: Darumaka
Flavor text: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokémon will immediately fall asleep.

Name: Darmanitan
Flavor text: The thick arms of this hot-blooded Pokémon can deliver punches capable of obliterating a dump truck.

Name: Maractus
Flavor text: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

Name: Dwebble
Flavor text: When it finds a stone appealing, it creates a hole inside it and uses it as its home. This Pokémon is the natural enemy of Roggenrola and Rolycoly.

Name: Crustle
Flavor text: This highly territorial Pokémon prefers dry climates. It won’t come out of its boulder on rainy days.

Name: Scraggy
Flavor text: If it locks eyes with you, watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokémon.

Name: Scrafty
Flavor text: As halfhearted as this Pokémon’s kicks may seem, they pack enough power to shatter Conkeldurr’s concrete pillars.

Name: Sigilyph
Flavor text: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians’ emissaries.

Name: Yamask
Flavor text: It wanders through ruins by night, carrying a mask that’s said to have been the face it had when it was still human.

Name: Cofagrigus
Flavor text: This Pokémon has a body of sparkling gold. People say it no longer remembers that it was once human.

Name: Tirtouga
Flavor text: This Pokémon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl, it still comes up onto land in search of prey.

Name: Carracosta
Flavor text: Carracosta completely devours its prey—bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta’s own shell grows thick and sturdy.

Name: Archen
Flavor text: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. As research suggested, Archen is unable to fly. But it’s very good at jumping.

Name: Archeops
Flavor text: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.

Name: Trubbish
Flavor text: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.

Name: Garbodor
Flavor text: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

Name: Zorua
Flavor text: Zorua is a timid Pokémon. This disposition seems to be what led to the development of Zorua’s ability to take on the forms of other creatures.

Name: Zoroark
Flavor text: This Pokémon cares deeply about others of its kind, and it will conjure terrifying illusions to keep its den and pack safe.

Name: Minccino
Flavor text: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

Name: Cinccino
Flavor text: Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won’t tolerate even a speck of the stuff.

Name: Gothita
Flavor text: Though they’re still only babies, there’s psychic power stored in their ribbonlike feelers, and sometimes they use that power to fight.

Name: Gothorita
Flavor text: It’s said that when stars shine in the night sky, this Pokémon will spirit away sleeping children. Some call it the Witch of Punishment.

Name: Gothitelle
Flavor text: It has tremendous psychic power, but it dislikes conflict. It’s also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.

Name: Solosis
Flavor text: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

Name: Duosion
Flavor text: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mile—but only if its two brains can agree with each other.

Name: Reuniclus
Flavor text: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokémon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.

Name: Ducklett
Flavor text: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water, escaping under cover of the spray.

Name: Swanna
Flavor text: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

Name: Vanillite
Flavor text: Unable to survive in hot areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.

Name: Vanillish
Flavor text: By drinking pure water, it grows its icy body. This Pokémon can be hard to find on days with warm, sunny weather.

Name: Vanilluxe
Flavor text: When its anger reaches a breaking point, this Pokémon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it, be they friend or foe.

Name: Deerling
Flavor text: Their coloring changes according to the seasons and can be slightly affected by the temperature and humidity as well.

Name: Sawsbuck
Flavor text: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

Name: Emolga
Flavor text: As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles with electricity. This Pokémon is cute, but it can cause a lot of trouble.

Name: Karrablast
Flavor text: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

Name: Escavalier
Flavor text: They use shells they’ve stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They’re very popular Pokémon in the Galar region.

Name: Foongus
Flavor text: No one knows what the Poké Ball–like pattern on Foongus means or why Foongus has it.

Name: Amoonguss
Flavor text: This Pokémon puffs poisonous spores at its foes. If the spores aren’t washed off quickly, they’ll grow into mushrooms wherever they land.

Name: Frillish
Flavor text: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps, five miles below the ocean’s surface.

Name: Jellicent
Flavor text: Most of this Pokémon’s body composition is identical to sea water. It makes sunken ships its lair.

Name: Alomomola
Flavor text: Fishermen take them along on long voyages, because if you have an Alomomola with you, there’ll be no need for a doctor or medicine.

Name: Joltik
Flavor text: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It’s soaking up static electricity because it can’t produce a charge on its own.

Name: Galvantula
Flavor text: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

Name: Ferroseed
Flavor text: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn’t very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.

Name: Ferrothorn
Flavor text: This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

Name: Klink
Flavor text: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

Name: Klang
Flavor text: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon’s rotation speed increases sharply.

Name: Klinklang
Flavor text: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

Name: Tynamo
Flavor text: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

Name: Eelektrik
Flavor text: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.

Name: Eelektross
Flavor text: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.

Name: Elgyem
Flavor text: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

Name: Beheeyem
Flavor text: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.

Name: Litwick
Flavor text: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.

Name: Lampent
Flavor text: This Pokémon appears just before someone passes away, so it’s feared as an emissary of death.

Name: Chandelure
Flavor text: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

Name: Axew
Flavor text: These Pokémon nest in the ground and use their tusks to crush hard berries. Crushing berries is also how they test each other’s strength.

Name: Fraxure
Flavor text: After battle, this Pokémon carefully sharpens its tusks on river rocks. It needs to take care of its tusks—if one breaks, it will never grow back.

Name: Haxorus
Flavor text: Its resilient tusks are its pride and joy. It licks up dirt to take in the minerals it needs to keep its tusks in top condition.

Name: Cubchoo
Flavor text: When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn’t like.

Name: Beartic
Flavor text: It swims through frigid seas, searching for prey. From its frozen breath, it forms icy fangs that are harder than steel.

Name: Cryogonal
Flavor text: With its icy chains, Cryogonal freezes those it encounters. It then takes its victims away to somewhere unknown.

Name: Shelmet
Flavor text: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.

Name: Accelgor
Flavor text: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

Name: Stunfisk
Flavor text: Thanks to bacteria that lived in the mud flats with it, this Pokémon developed the organs it uses to generate electricity.

Name: Mienfoo
Flavor text: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.

Name: Mienshao
Flavor text: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

Name: Druddigon
Flavor text: Druddigon lives in caves, but it never skips sunbathing—it won’t be able to move if its body gets too cold.

Name: Golett
Flavor text: They were sculpted from clay in ancient times. No one knows why, but some of them are driven to continually line up boulders.

Name: Golurk
Flavor text: Artillery platforms built into the walls of ancient castles served as perches from which Golurk could fire energy beams.

Name: Pawniard
Flavor text: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.

Name: Bisharp
Flavor text: It’s accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.

Name: Bouffalant
Flavor text: These Pokémon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.

Name: Rufflet
Flavor text: If it spies a strong Pokémon, Rufflet can’t resist challenging it to a battle. But if Rufflet loses, it starts bawling.

Name: Braviary
Flavor text: Known for its bravery and pride, this majestic Pokémon is often seen as a motif for various kinds of emblems.

Name: Vullaby
Flavor text: It wears a bone to protect its rear. It often squabbles with others of its kind over particularly comfy bones.

Name: Mandibuzz
Flavor text: Although it’s a bit of a ruffian, this Pokémon will take lost Vullaby under its wing and care for them till they’re ready to leave the nest.

Name: Heatmor
Flavor text: There’s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

Name: Durant
Flavor text: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.

Name: Deino
Flavor text: When it encounters something, its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes, it will commit the associated scent to memory.

Name: Zweilous
Flavor text: While hunting for prey, Zweilous wanders its territory, its two heads often bickering over which way to go.

Name: Hydreigon
Flavor text: There are a slew of stories about villages that were destroyed by Hydreigon. It bites anything that moves.

Name: Larvesta
Flavor text: The people of ancient times believed that Larvesta fell from the sun.

Name: Volcarona
Flavor text: Volcarona scatters burning scales. Some say it does this to start fires. Others say it’s trying to rescue those that suffer in the cold.

Name: Cobalion
Flavor text: This Pokémon appears in a legend alongside Terrakion and Virizion, fighting against humans in defense of the Unova region’s Pokémon.

Name: Terrakion
Flavor text: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokémon.

Name: Virizion
Flavor text: A legend tells of this Pokémon working together with Cobalion and Terrakion to protect the Pokémon of the Unova region.

Name: Tornadus
Flavor text: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

Name: Thundurus
Flavor text: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

Name: Reshiram
Flavor text: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

Name: Zekrom
Flavor text: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.

Name: Landorus
Flavor text: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

Name: Kyurem
Flavor text: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.

Name: Keldeo
Flavor text: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

Name: Meloetta
Flavor text: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

Name: Genesect
Flavor text: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

Name: Chespin
Flavor text: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

Name: Quilladin
Flavor text: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

Name: Chesnaught
Flavor text: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

Name: Fennekin
Flavor text: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Braixen
Flavor text: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

Name: Delphox
Flavor text: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

Name: Froakie
Flavor text: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

Name: Frogadier
Flavor text: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

Name: Greninja
Flavor text: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

Name: Bunnelby
Flavor text: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.

Name: Diggersby
Flavor text: With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It’s a huge help during tunnel construction.

Name: Fletchling
Flavor text: Its melodious cries are actually warnings. Fletchling will mercilessly peck at anything that enters its territory.

Name: Fletchinder
Flavor text: Fletchinder launches embers into the den of its prey. When the prey comes leaping out, Fletchinder’s sharp talons finish it off.

Name: Talonflame
Flavor text: Talonflame mainly preys upon other bird Pokémon. To intimidate opponents, it sends embers spewing from gaps between its feathers.

Name: Scatterbug
Flavor text: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

Name: Spewpa
Flavor text: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

Name: Vivillon
Flavor text: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

Name: Litleo
Flavor text: When they’re young, they live with a pride. Once they’re able to hunt prey on their own, they’re kicked out and have to make their own way.

Name: Pyroar
Flavor text: The males are usually lazy, but when attacked by a strong foe, a male will protect its friends with no regard for its own safety.

Name: Flabébé
Flavor text: It’s not safe without the power of a flower, but it will keep traveling around until it finds one with the color and shape it wants.

Name: Floette
Flavor text: It raises flowers and uses them as weapons. The more gorgeous the blossom, the more power it contains.

Name: Florges
Flavor text: It controls the flowers it grows. The petal blizzards that Florges triggers are overwhelming in their beauty and power.

Name: Skiddo
Flavor text: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

Name: Gogoat
Flavor text: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

Name: Pancham
Flavor text: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master’s actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.

Name: Pangoro
Flavor text: This Pokémon is quick to anger, and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.

Name: Furfrou
Flavor text: There was an era when aristocrats would compete to see who could trim their Furfrou’s fur into the most exquisite style.

Name: Espurr
Flavor text: Though Espurr’s expression never changes, behind that blank stare is an intense struggle to contain its devastating psychic power.

Name: Meowstic
Flavor text: Revealing the eyelike patterns on the insides of its ears will unleash its psychic powers. It normally keeps the patterns hidden, however.

Name: Honedge
Flavor text: Honedge’s soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge’s body.

Name: Doublade
Flavor text: Honedge evolves into twins. The two blades rub together to emit a metallic sound that unnerves opponents.

Name: Aegislash
Flavor text: In this defensive stance, Aegislash uses its steel body and a force field of spectral power to reduce the damage of any attack.

Name: Spritzee
Flavor text: A scent pouch within this Pokémon’s body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.

Name: Aromatisse
Flavor text: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokémon’s companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.

Name: Swirlix
Flavor text: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn’t get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.

Name: Slurpuff
Flavor text: By taking in a person’s scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

Name: Inkay
Flavor text: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

Name: Malamar
Flavor text: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar’s control.

Name: Binacle
Flavor text: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

Name: Barbaracle
Flavor text: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

Name: Skrelp
Flavor text: It drifts in the ocean, blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokémon come to feast on the seaweed, Skrelp feasts on them instead.

Name: Dragalge
Flavor text: Dragalge uses a poisonous liquid capable of corroding metal to send tankers that enter its territory to the bottom of the sea.

Name: Clauncher
Flavor text: Clauncher’s claws can fall off during battle, but they’ll regenerate. The meat inside the claws is popular as a delicacy in Galar.

Name: Clawitzer
Flavor text: After using the feelers on its oversized claw to detect the location of prey, Clawitzer launches a cannonball of water at its target.

Name: Helioptile
Flavor text: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon’s electric moves.

Name: Heliolisk
Flavor text: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokémon. Appropriately, when Heliolisk came to the Galar region, treasure came with them.

Name: Tyrunt
Flavor text: This is an ancient Pokémon, revived in modern times. It has a violent disposition, and it’ll tear apart anything it gets between its hefty jaws.

Name: Tyrantrum
Flavor text: This Pokémon is from about 100,000,000 years ago. It has the presence of a king, vicious but magnificent.

Name: Amaura
Flavor text: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past, it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.

Name: Aurorus
Flavor text: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It’s said that when this Pokémon howls, auroras appear in the night sky.

Name: Sylveon
Flavor text: By releasing enmity-erasing waves from its ribbonlike feelers, Sylveon stops any conflict.

Name: Hawlucha
Flavor text: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.

Name: Dedenne
Flavor text: A Dedenne’s whiskers pick up electrical waves other Dedenne send out. These Pokémon share locations of food or electricity with one another.

Name: Carbink
Flavor text: When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all out by firing high-energy beams from the gems embedded in its body.

Name: Goomy
Flavor text: Because most of its body is water, it will dry up if the weather becomes too arid. It’s considered the weakest dragon Pokémon.

Name: Sliggoo
Flavor text: Although this Pokémon isn’t very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it.

Name: Goodra
Flavor text: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don’t mind, finding this behavior to be adorable.

Name: Klefki
Flavor text: This Pokémon is constantly collecting keys. Entrust a Klefki with important keys, and the Pokémon will protect them no matter what.

Name: Phantump
Flavor text: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit’s rebirth as this Pokémon.

Name: Trevenant
Flavor text: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

Name: Pumpkaboo
Flavor text: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
Flavor text: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

Name: Bergmite
Flavor text: They chill the air around them to −150 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing the water in the air into ice that they use as armor.

Name: Avalugg
Flavor text: At high latitudes, this Pokémon can be found with clusters of Bergmite on its back as it swims among the icebergs.

Name: Noibat
Flavor text: After nightfall, they emerge from the caves they nest in during the day. Using their ultrasonic waves, they go on the hunt for ripened fruit.

Name: Noivern
Flavor text: Aggressive and cruel, this Pokémon will ruthlessly torment enemies that are helpless in the dark.

Name: Xerneas
Flavor text: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

Name: Yveltal
Flavor text: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

Name: Zygarde
Flavor text: This is Zygarde’s form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem.

Name: Diancie
Flavor text: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

Name: Hoopa
Flavor text: In its true form, it possesses a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.

Name: Volcanion
Flavor text: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

Name: Rowlet
Flavor text: It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.

Name: Dartrix
Flavor text: This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don’t groom it diligently, it will stop listening to you.

Name: Decidueye
Flavor text: It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can’t afford to miss, it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.

Name: Litten
Flavor text: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

Name: Torracat
Flavor text: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer’s whole body covered in scratches.

Name: Incineroar
Flavor text: Although it’s rough mannered and egotistical, it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

Name: Popplio
Flavor text: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

Name: Brionne
Flavor text: It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn’t know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.

Name: Primarina
Flavor text: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

Name: Pikipek
Flavor text: It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

Name: Trumbeak
Flavor text: It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.

Name: Toucannon
Flavor text: They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

Name: Yungoos
Flavor text: Its stomach takes up most of its long torso. It’s a big eater, so the amount Trainers have to spend on its food is no laughing matter.

Name: Gumshoos
Flavor text: Although it wasn’t originally found in Alola, this Pokémon was brought over a long time ago when there was a huge Rattata outbreak.

Name: Grubbin
Flavor text: Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

Name: Charjabug
Flavor text: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

Name: Vikavolt
Flavor text: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.

Name: Crabrawler
Flavor text: Its hard pincers are well suited to both offense and defense. Fights between two Crabrawler are like boxing matches.

Name: Crabominable
Flavor text: It stores coldness in its pincers and pummels its foes. It can even smash thick walls of ice to bits!

Name: Oricorio
Flavor text: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.

Name: Cutiefly
Flavor text: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. You can find Cutiefly hovering around Gossifleur, trying to get some of Gossifleur’s pollen.

Name: Ribombee
Flavor text: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs’ effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.

Name: Rockruff
Flavor text: This Pokémon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.

Name: Lycanroc
Flavor text: This Lycanroc is calm and cautious. The rocks jutting from its mane are razor sharp.

Name: Wishiwashi
Flavor text: Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

Name: Mareanie
Flavor text: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it’s impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.

Name: Toxapex
Flavor text: To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokémon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.

Name: Mudbray
Flavor text: Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokémon. It’s skilled at making use of mud.

Name: Mudsdale
Flavor text: Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale’s legs sets harder than stone. It’s so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.

Name: Dewpider
Flavor text: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

Name: Araquanid
Flavor text: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

Name: Fomantis
Flavor text: When bathed in sunlight, this Pokémon emits a pleasantly sweet scent, which causes bug Pokémon to gather around it.

Name: Lurantis
Flavor text: This Pokémon resembles a beautiful flower. A properly raised Lurantis will have gorgeous, brilliant colors.

Name: Morelull
Flavor text: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull’s head. The caps regrow overnight.

Name: Shiinotic
Flavor text: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

Name: Salandit
Flavor text: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokémon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit’s poisonous gas.

Name: Salazzle
Flavor text: Only female Salazzle exist. They emit a gas laden with pheromones to captivate male Salandit.

Name: Stufful
Flavor text: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

Name: Bewear
Flavor text: Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

Name: Bounsweet
Flavor text: Its body gives off a sweet, fruity scent that is extremely appetizing to bird Pokémon.

Name: Steenee
Flavor text: As it twirls like a dancer, a sweet smell spreads out around it. Anyone who inhales the scent will feel a surge of happiness.

Name: Tsareena
Flavor text: This feared Pokémon has long, slender legs and a cruel heart. It shows no mercy as it stomps on its opponents.

Name: Comfey
Flavor text: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won’t wither once they’re attached to a Comfey.

Name: Oranguru
Flavor text: With waves of its fan—made from leaves and its own fur—Oranguru skillfully gives instructions to other Pokémon.

Name: Passimian
Flavor text: Displaying amazing teamwork, they follow the orders of their boss as they all help out in the search for their favorite berries.

Name: Wimpod
Flavor text: It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.

Name: Golisopod
Flavor text: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

Name: Sandygast
Flavor text: Grudges of the dead have possessed a mound of sand and become a Pokémon. Sandygast is fond of the shovel on its head.

Name: Palossand
Flavor text: Palossand is known as the Beach Nightmare. It pulls its prey down into the sand by controlling the sand itself, and then it sucks out their souls.

Name: Pyukumuku
Flavor text: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

Name: Type: Null
Flavor text: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokémon being created in the Galar region.

Name: Silvally
Flavor text: A solid bond of trust between this Pokémon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

Name: Minior
Flavor text: It lives in the ozone layer, where it becomes food for stronger Pokémon. When it tries to run away, it falls to the ground.

Name: Komala
Flavor text: It stays asleep from the moment it’s born. When it falls into a deep sleep, it stops moving altogether.

Name: Turtonator
Flavor text: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

Name: Togedemaru
Flavor text: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

Name: Mimikyu
Flavor text: It wears a rag fashioned into a Pikachu costume in an effort to look less scary. Unfortunately, the costume only makes it creepier.

Name: Bruxish
Flavor text: It burrows beneath the sand, radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.

Name: Drampa
Flavor text: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

Name: Dhelmise
Flavor text: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

Name: Jangmo-o
Flavor text: They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together. The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.

Name: Hakamo-o
Flavor text: The scaleless, scarred parts of its body are signs of its strength. It shows them off to defeated opponents.

Name: Kommo-o
Flavor text: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

Name: Tapu Koko
Flavor text: Although it’s called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

Name: Tapu Lele
Flavor text: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

Name: Tapu Bulu
Flavor text: Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

Name: Tapu Fini
Flavor text: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

Name: Cosmog
Flavor text: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.

Name: Cosmoem
Flavor text: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the “cocoon of the stars” and built an altar to worship it.

Name: Solgaleo
Flavor text: Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.

Name: Lunala
Flavor text: Records of it exist in writings from long, long ago, where it was known by the name “the beast that calls the moon.”

Name: Nihilego
Flavor text: A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

Name: Buzzwole
Flavor text: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Pheromosa
Flavor text: A life-form that lives in another world, its body is thin and supple, but it also possesses great power.

Name: Xurkitree
Flavor text: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Celesteela
Flavor text: One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.

Name: Kartana
Flavor text: This Ultra Beast’s body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

Name: Guzzlord
Flavor text: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here, it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Necrozma
Flavor text: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It’s apparently from another world.

Name: Magearna
Flavor text: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.

Name: Marshadow
Flavor text: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.

Name: Poipole
Flavor text: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

Name: Naganadel
Flavor text: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

Name: Stakataka
Flavor text: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

Name: Blacephalon
Flavor text: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

Name: Zeraora
Flavor text: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

Name: Meltan
Flavor text: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

Name: Melmetal
Flavor text: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

Name: Grookey
Flavor text: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

Name: Thwackey
Flavor text: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

Name: Rillaboom
Flavor text: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

Name: Scorbunny
Flavor text: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon’s body. Once that happens, it’s ready to fight at full power.

Name: Raboot
Flavor text: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

Name: Cinderace
Flavor text: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

Name: Sobble
Flavor text: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won’t be able to resist weeping.

Name: Drizzile
Flavor text: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

Name: Inteleon
Flavor text: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

Name: Skwovet
Flavor text: Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.

Name: Greedent
Flavor text: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn’t notice the loss.

Name: Rookidee
Flavor text: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

Name: Corvisquire
Flavor text: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

Name: Corviknight
Flavor text: This Pokémon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.

Name: Blipbug
Flavor text: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn’t.

Name: Dottler
Flavor text: It barely moves, but it’s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

Name: Orbeetle
Flavor text: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

Name: Nickit
Flavor text: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

Name: Thievul
Flavor text: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

Name: Gossifleur
Flavor text: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

Name: Eldegoss
Flavor text: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

Name: Wooloo
Flavor text: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

Name: Dubwool
Flavor text: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

Name: Chewtle
Flavor text: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

Name: Drednaw
Flavor text: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

Name: Yamper
Flavor text: This Pokémon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs, it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

Name: Boltund
Flavor text: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

Name: Rolycoly
Flavor text: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

Name: Carkol
Flavor text: It forms coal inside its body. Coal dropped by this Pokémon once helped fuel the lives of people in the Galar region.

Name: Coalossal
Flavor text: It’s usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Applin
Flavor text: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it’s just an apple and nothing more.

Name: Flapple
Flavor text: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

Name: Appletun
Flavor text: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

Name: Silicobra
Flavor text: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

Name: Sandaconda
Flavor text: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

Name: Cramorant
Flavor text: It’s so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it’s battling midfight.

Name: Arrokuda
Flavor text: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It’s very proud of that jaw.

Name: Barraskewda
Flavor text: This Pokémon has a jaw that’s as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda’s flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.

Name: Toxel
Flavor text: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

Name: Toxtricity
Flavor text: Capable of generating 15,000 volts of electricity, this Pokémon looks down on all that would challenge it.

Name: Sizzlipede
Flavor text: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

Name: Centiskorch
Flavor text: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

Name: Clobbopus
Flavor text: It’s very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

Name: Grapploct
Flavor text: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

Name: Sinistea
Flavor text: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

Name: Polteageist
Flavor text: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.

Name: Hatenna
Flavor text: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures’ emotions. If you don’t have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

Name: Hattrem
Flavor text: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

Name: Hatterene
Flavor text: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

Name: Impidimp
Flavor text: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

Name: Morgrem
Flavor text: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it’s trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

Name: Grimmsnarl
Flavor text: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

Name: Obstagoon
Flavor text: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.

Name: Perrserker
Flavor text: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

Name: Cursola
Flavor text: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon’s core spirit.

Name: Sirfetch'd
Flavor text: Only Farfetch’d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon’s leek withers, it will retire from combat.

Name: Mr. Rime
Flavor text: It’s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

Name: Runerigus
Flavor text: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

Name: Milcery
Flavor text: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

Name: Alcremie
Flavor text: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.

Name: Falinks
Flavor text: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass’s orders are absolute.

Name: Pincurchin
Flavor text: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

Name: Snom
Flavor text: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

Name: Frosmoth
Flavor text: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than −290 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Stonjourner
Flavor text: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun’s descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

Name: Eiscue
Flavor text: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.

Name: Indeedee
Flavor text: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.

Name: Morpeko
Flavor text: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It’s also generating electricity.

Name: Cufant
Flavor text: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It’s also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

Name: Copperajah
Flavor text: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

Name: Dracozolt
Flavor text: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

Name: Arctozolt
Flavor text: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

Name: Dracovish
Flavor text: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

Name: Arctovish
Flavor text: Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

Name: Duraludon
Flavor text: Its body resembles polished metal, and it’s both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

Name: Dreepy
Flavor text: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

Name: Drakloak
Flavor text: It’s capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

Name: Dragapult
Flavor text: When it isn’t battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

Name: Zacian
Flavor text: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

Name: Zamazenta
Flavor text: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

Name: Eternatus
Flavor text: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

Name: Kubfu
Flavor text: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

Name: Urshifu
Flavor text: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

Name: Zarude
Flavor text: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

Name: Regieleki
Flavor text: This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It’s said that removing the rings on Regieleki’s body will unleash the Pokémon’s latent power.

Name: Regidrago
Flavor text: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago’s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory remains unproven.

Name: Glastrier
Flavor text: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It’s also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.

Name: Spectrier
Flavor text: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn’t use its sense of sight. Spectrier’s kicks are said to separate soul from body.

Name: Calyrex
Flavor text: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.
